THE AIRCRAFEET DEPD MIAMI AT NGT ON AN ON-DEMAND, AIR TAXI FLIGHT TO FEET MYERS, FL.  
DURING ARRIVAL AT THE DESTN, THE FLIGHT ENCTRD IFR CONDS. THE PILOT OBTAINED 
CLNC FOR AN ILS RUNWAY 6 APPROACH AND WAS TOLD TO RPRT AT THE OUTER MARKER (OM). 
AT 0152:25 EST, HE RPRTD TO MIAMI CENTER THAT HE WAS OVER THE OM.  THIS 
WAS HIS LAST TRANSMISSION TO AN AIR TRAFFIC CONTROL FACILITY.  AT ABOUT 0203 EST, HE MADE A 
TRANSMISSION ON UNICOM FREQ TO INFORM ARPT OPNS PSNL THAT HE COULD 
NOT GET THE APPROACH LIGHTS TO OPERATE.  HE WAS ASKED IF HE HAD USED THE 
PROPER FREQ AND HAD KEYED THE MIKE THE REQUIRED NUMBER OF TIMES.  THE PILOT 
INDCD THAT HE HAD PROPERLY KEYED THE MIKE; HOWEVER, UNICOM PSNL DID 
NOT HEAR ANY KEYING OF THE MIKE EXCEPT FOR 2 CLICKS.  THE AIRCRAFT CTCD THE 
GND IN A NRLY LEVEL ATTITUDE AND WITH THE GEAR EXTENDED, APPROXIMATELY 1.5 MI SHORT 
OF RUNWAY 6.  IT THEN SKIDDED ABOUT 90 FEET AND HIT A TREE BEFORE COMING TO REST.  
NO PREIMPACT PART FAILURE/MALFUNCTION WAS FND WITH THE AIRCRAFT, ENG OR 
APCH/RUNWAY LIGHTS. THE 0149 EST WX AT FEET MYERS WAS IN PART:  SKY OBSCURED, 
VIS 1/4 MI WITH FOG. 
FAILURE OF THE PILOT TO PROPERLY FOLLOW THE IFR PROCEDURE AND TO 
IDENTIFY THE DECISION HEIGHT.  FACTORS RELATED TO THE ACCIDENT WERE:  
THE ADVERSE WEATHER CONDITIONS, DARKNESS, THE PILOT'S LACK OF VISUAL 
PERCEPTION WITHOUT THE APPROACH LIGHTS, AND TREE(S) IN THE ACCIDENT 
AREA. 
